[The report is actually not the 1st Latin American case of infection due to this organism, but rather the 1st with fungemia in Latin America and is published as: Orecchini LA, Olmos E, Taverna CG, et al. First Latin American case of fungemia due to _Pseudozyma aphidis_ in a pediatric patient with osteosarcoma. J Clin Microbiol. 2015 Aug 19. pii: JCM.01095-15.

_Pseudozyma_ spp. are yeast-like fungi, classified in the Ustilaginales, which are mostly epiphytic or saprophytic and are not generally pathogenic to plants. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3687429,4.]

